Catcord â€“ Admin Guide

Operations and configuration guide for Discord server administrators.

Overview

Catcord enables seamless multilingual conversations by relaying and translating messages between language-specific channels. Mirrored messages are posted via webhooks using each authorâ€™s display name and avatar, so they appear as normal user messages (no BOT tag).

  • Cross-channel relay with optional translation (DeepL / OpenAI)
  • Optional thread mirroring and reply-context line
  • Attachment mirroring
  • Per-guild persistent configuration and access control

Quick Start

  1. Give the bot these permissions in every target channel: Send Messages, Manage Webhooks, Read Message History, and if using threads: Create Public Threads.
  2. Map your language channels: 
    /langrelay_set channel:#german language:DE
/langrelay_set channel:#english language:EN
/langrelay_set channel:#french language:FR
  3. Select a translation provider: 
    /langrelay_provider provider:deepl  # or: openai
  4. (Optional) Enable features: 
    /langrelay_replymode state:on
/langrelay_thread_mirroring state:on
  5. Verify settings: 
    /langrelay_status
Tip: You can manage who is allowed to configure Catcord using the access-control commands listed below.

Environment

Create a .env file with:

DISCORD_TOKEN=your-discord-bot-token
DEEPL_TOKEN=your-deepl-key   # optional
OPENAI_TOKEN=your-openai-key # optional
LANGRELAY_WEBHOOK_NAME=Catcord

You can run with either DeepL or OpenAI; choose per guild using /langrelay_provider.

Options & Behavior

  • Invisible posting: Mirrored messages are posted via per-channel webhooks with the authorâ€™s name and avatar.
  • Loop protection: Messages posted by webhooks are ignored to prevent relay loops.
  • Reply mode: Adds a short translated line referencing the replied message (if enabled).
  • Thread mirroring: Creates/reopens same-named public threads in target channels and posts inside them (if enabled and permitted).
  • Attachments: Up to 10 attachments are downloaded and re-uploaded to targets.
  • Mentions: Mentions are sanitized to avoid cross-channel pinging.

Troubleshooting

  • Nothing is mirrored: Check mappings with /langrelay_status and verify Manage Webhooks permission.
  • Translation errors or rate limits: Verify API keys and switch provider with /langrelay_provider if needed.
  • Thread mirroring not working: Ensure the bot can create public threads in all target channels.
  • â€œNoneType object is not iterableâ€ in logs: Use the latest cog; safe-send helpers avoid passing files=None to thread sends.

Security & Policy

  • Webhook â€œimpersonationâ€ is used to keep relays unobtrusive. Consider noting this in channel topics or server rules.
  • Do not use Catcord to forge identities outside the translation/relay context.
